				\begin{document}$${\rm{Information}}\,{\rm{Gain}}({\rm{Class}},{\rm{Feature}})={\rm{H}}({\rm{Class}})-{\rm{H}}({\rm{Class}}|{\rm{Feature}})$$\end{document}InformationGain(Class,Feature)=H(Class)−H(Class|Feature)

In this equation, H is information entropy defined by Eq. 2.2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
