				\begin{document}$$H(X)={E}_{x}[I(x)]=-{\sum }_{x\in X}p(x)\mathrm{log}\,p(x)$$\end{document}H(X)=Ex[I(x)]=−∑x∈Xp(x)logp(x)where p(x) is the probability of x and E(x) shows the expected value. Information entropy indicates the uncertainty associated with a random feature. In other words, information gain measures the expected reduction in uncertainty using a specific feature to predict a class37, 38.

